parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop lamp switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, it can also affect the anti-lock braking system (ABS) and traction control mechanisms, which can compromise vehicle safety and stability.
symptoms: Brake lights do not function or are intermittent
ABS and traction control systems malfunction

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to use the special spare nuts can cause the wheel mounts to lock, leading to brake engagement, loss of control, and potential accidents. Additionally, the lack of warning labels on the spare tire can contribute to this failure.
